<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
This document is meant to be the all-inclusive definition of attributes in the project.

Open RPG Maker has each attribute definition in its own XML file, but each file is only one node with attributes; in my
XML file format, and subsequent encrypted gaming data, it is better to keep together all attributes defined in this one
XML file (to reduce the number of files).

Each attribute is specified as belonging to a class (either magic or weapon), has an identifier, percentile multipliers
(tiers A, B, C, D, E), and finally has a title and a type-icon.

In this case, the iconset and the id fields are the only ones that are new &mdash; the former, for editor controls; the
latter, for the default icon shown in menu screens.

The first child node is for including some defaults for the editor to use when computing new attributes; these item are
for the editor's use only, and will not go into the game data. We only have a default value for a default iconset; each
attribute may select a specific icon tile number. Also, the defaults for the multipliers are normally expected to be in
descending order of magnitude; values such as "200 150 100 50 0" (a value for each multiplier, respectively) are a good
baseline for default attributes; a discerning game creator can alter their values to suit their needs.
-->
<beyondrm-attributes>
  <attribute-defaults iconset="0" multA="200" multB="150" multC="100" multD="50" multE="0" />
  <attribute-list>
    <attribute attclass="mg" iconset="" icon-id="" id="AttrMag00" title="Fire" >
      <attr-multiipliers multiplier-A="200" multiplier-B="150" multiplier-C="100" multiplier-D="50" multiplier-E="0" />
    </attribute>
    <attribute attclass="mg" iconset="" icon-id="" id="AttrMag01" title="Thunder" >
